############################################# ### Generated from PreTeXt source ### ### https://pretextbook.org ### ############################################# ## DBsubject() ## DBchapter() ## DBsection() ## Level() ## KEYWORDS() ## TitleText1() ## EditionText1() ## AuthorText1() ## Section1(not reported) ## Problem1(1.2.9.157) ## Author() ## Institution() ## Language(en-US)
DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "parserFormulaWithUnits.pl", "contextForm.pl", "contextFraction.pl", "randomPerson.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ $p = randomPerson(); $building = random(30,80,2); $model = random(2,10); Context("Fraction"); $ans = $model/($building)*5.5; $answer = FormulaWithUnits("$ans in"); @aux[0] = 5.5*$model;
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML [$p] is an architect and [$p->they] [$p->are] making a scale model of a building. The actual building will be [`[$building]`] ft tall. In the model, the height of the building will be [`[$model]`] in tall and there will be a little model person standing next to the building. How tall should [$p] make the model of that person who is meant to represent a [`5`] ft [`6`] in tall person?
[_]{$answer}{16}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION Let [`h`] be the height of the person in [$p]'s model, which we'll measure in inches. We'll create a proportional equation that compares the building and person's heights in the model to their heights in real life:
[```\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \frac{\text{height of model building in inches}}{\text{height of actual building in feet}}\amp=\frac{\text{height of model person in inches}}{\text{height of actual person in feet}}\\ \frac{[$model]\,\text{in}}{[$building]\,\text{ft}}\amp=\frac{h\,\text{in}}{5\,\text{ft}\,6\text{in}} \end{aligned} ```]
Before we can just eliminate the units, we'll need to convert 5 ft[$NBSP]*6 in to feet:
[``` \frac{2\,\text{in}}{30\,\text{ft}}=\frac{h\,\text{in}}{5.5\,\text{ft}} ```]
Now we can remove the units and continue solving:
[```\newcommand{\multiplyright}[2][\cdot]{{\highlight{{{}#1#2}}}}\newcommand{\multiplyleft}[2][\cdot]{{\highlight{{#2#1{}}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \frac{[$model]}{[$building]}\amp=\frac{h}{5.5}\\ \multiplyleft{[$building]\cdot5.5}\frac{[$model]}{[$building]}\amp=\frac{h}{5.5}\multiplyright{[$building]\cdot5.5}\\ 5.5\cdot [$model] \amp= [$building]h\\ [$aux[0]] \amp= [$building]h\\ h\amp\approx [$ans] \end{aligned} ```]
[$p] should make the model be [`[$answer]`] tall.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
ENDDOCUMENT();
